  "prompt": "My iPhone screen broke I have iCloud, would notifications I received transfer over to a replacement or would contacts transfer and notifications gone?",
  "response": "When you get a replacement iPhone and restore from your iCloud backup, here is what will happen:\n\n1. **Contacts:** Your contacts will transfer over to the new device as they are typically synced and stored in iCloud.\n\n2. **Notifications:** Specific notifications that you had received on your broken iPhone will **not** transfer over to the replacement device. Notifications are generally not included in the iCloud backup. Once you set up your new iPhone, you'll start receiving new notifications just as you did before, but past notifications cannot be restored.\n\nOther data such as photos, messages, app data, and settings will be restored from your iCloud backup, allowing you to pick up where you left off in other aspects of phone use.",
